<P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#120;</FONT> Rule 13p-1 under the<I> Securities Exchange Act</I> (17 CFR 240.13p-1) for the reporting
period from January&nbsp;1 to December&nbsp;31, 2014. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:22pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>Section&nbsp;1 &#150; Conflict Minerals Disclosure </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>Item&nbsp;1.01 Conflict Minerals Disclosure and Report </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>Alcatel-Lucent Company Profile </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Alcatel-Lucent may be
referred to as &#147;Alcatel-Lucent&#148;, &#147;we,&#148; &#147;us&#148; or &#147;our&#148;. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">As the leading specialist in IP networking, ultra-broadband
access and cloud technology, Alcatel-Lucent is dedicated to making global communications more innovative, sustainable and accessible for people, businesses and governments around the world. We call this &#145;responsible business innovation&#146;
&#151; and it is our mission to invent and deliver dependable, large-scale networks that increase the capacity and reach of communications technologies, ultimately changing the way billions of people live and do business. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">With revenues of &#128;13.2 billion in 2014, Alcatel-Lucent is listed on the Paris and New York stock exchanges (Euronext and NYSE: ALU). The company is
incorporated in France and headquartered in Boulogne-Billancourt. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>Conflict Minerals and Reasonable Country of Origin Inquiry (RCOI) </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">In accordance with the company&#146;s own Conflict Minerals Policy (which is publicly available on its website) and the rules promulgated by the U.S.
Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC), Alcatel-Lucent has undertaken a multi-step process to determine the level of disclosure required regarding conflict minerals (as defined under Section&nbsp;1502 of the U.S. <I>Dodd&#150;Frank Wall Street
Reform and Consumer Protection Act</I>). </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">We have determined that our company manufactures (or contracts to manufacture) products for which conflict
minerals are necessary to their components&#146; functionality or production. As such, we conducted a good faith &#145;reasonable country of origin inquiry&#146; (RCOI) to determine whether our necessary conflict minerals originated in the
Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC) or an adjoining country (collectively referred to in this Form as the &#147;Covered Countries&#148;) or came from recycled/scrap resources. </P>

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">As explained more fully in the attached Conflict Minerals Report, our RCOI process relied primarily on supplier
and smelter representations regarding the origin of their minerals. We identified certain purchased commodities or components used in our products as necessary to survey and reasonably inquire into the nature and origin of their material content.
Information was then collected from targeted suppliers regarding the minerals used to manufacture their products, the smelters from whom they purchase the minerals and their conflict minerals policies and due diligence processes. In addition,
whenever possible, the identified smelters&#146; country of origin information was collected from the Conflict Free Smelters Initiative (CFSI). Throughout this process, we used the CFSI&#146;s Conflict Minerals Reporting Template (CMRT) to
facilitate the transfer of information throughout the supply chain and collect conflict minerals traceability information from our suppliers. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">For 2014,
we determined the minerals used in our products originated from the following categories in which countries of origin have been grouped within CFSI]: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:10pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="70%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt">

Belgium, Bolivia, Brazil, Canada, Chile, China, Columbia, C&ocirc;te d&#146;Ivoire, Czech Republic, Djibouti, Egypt, Estonia, Ethiopia, France, Germany, Guyana, Hungary, India, Indonesia, Ireland, Israel, Japan, Kazakhstan, Laos, Luxemburg,
Madagascar, Malaysia, Mongolia, Myanmar, Namibia, Netherlands, Nigeria, Peru, Portugal, Russia, Sierra Leone, Singapore, Slovakia, South Korea, Spain, Suriname, Switzerland, Taiwan, United Kingdom, United States of America, Vietnam,

<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"></TD>

Africa</P></TD></TR>

<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt">Level 3 countries</TD>

Republic, Republic of Congo, Rwanda, South Sudan, Tanzania, Uganda, Zambia</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt">DRC</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:8pt"> <P STYLE="margin-left:0.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Democratic Republic of
Congo</P></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:20pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">After determining the country of origin of the minerals used in our products, the next step involved due diligence into the
source of any conflict minerals. As explained in our Conflicts Minerals Report, Alcatel-Lucent designed its due diligence measures to conform in all material respects with the internationally recognized framework set forth in the Organization for
Economic Co-operation and Development (OECD) <I>Due Diligence Guidance for Responsible Supply Chains of Minerals from Conflict-Affected and High-Risk Areas </I>(2013)&nbsp;and its related supplements for gold, tin, tantalum and tungsten. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">As a result of our RCOI, we concluded that certain conflicts minerals may have originated from the Covered Countries, and may not have derived from recycled
or scrap materials. Further, as described in the attached 2014 Alcatel-Lucent Conflicts Minerals Report, despite a multi-step investigation and intensive due diligence, for many smelters identified in our supply chain, we have been unable to
determine whether or not any of the conflict minerals directly or indirectly benefited armed groups in the Covered Countries. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">We have attached Exhibit
1.01, the 2014 Alcatel-Lucent Conflict Minerals Report, which includes a description of the measures taken to exercise due diligence on the minerals&#146; source and chain of custody. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Our Conflict Minerals Report is also publicly available on here: http://resources.alcatel-lucent.com/?cid=169613. </P>

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>Item&nbsp;1.02 Exhibit </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Alcatel-Lucent Conflict Minerals Report is attached as Exhibit 1.01. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:20pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>Section&nbsp;2 &#150; Exhibits </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>Item&nbsp;2.01
Exhibit </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The following exhibit is filed as part of this report: </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Exhibit 1.01 &#150; Conflict Minerals Report (as required by Items 1.01 and 1.02 of this Form) </P>

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><B>SIGNATURES </B></P>

authorized undersigned. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:30pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

 <BODY BGCOLOR="WHITE">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><B>Exhibit 1.01 </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:30pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:30pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B>ALCATEL-LUCENT </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:30pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:30pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B>CONFLICT MINERALS REPORT
</B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:30pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:30pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B>2014 </B></P>

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:18pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>1. Introduction </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>1.1.
&nbsp;&nbsp;The conflict minerals issue </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">On August&nbsp;22, 2012, the United States Securities and Exchange Commission adopted Rule 13p-1 under
Section&nbsp;13(p) of the <I>Securities Exchange Act</I>, defining &#145;conflict minerals&#146; as tin, tantalum, tungsten and gold that originate from the Democratic Republic of Congo and its adjoining countries (Angola, Burundi, Central African
Republic, Republic of the Congo, Rwanda, South Sudan, Tanzania, Uganda and Zambia). </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">It has been reported that the metals extracted from several
mines in this region benefit armed groups &#151; either directly or indirectly &#151; whose activities result in human rights violations and/or significant environmental damage. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>1.2. &nbsp;&nbsp;How Alcatel-Lucent is affected by conflict minerals </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">As the leading specialist in IP networking, ultra-broadband access and cloud technology, Alcatel-Lucent commonly uses tin, tantalum, tungsten and gold in
the electronic components and parts comprising its telecommunications equipment. Under Rule 13p-1, companies such as Alcatel-Lucent are required to take steps to determine the origin of the tin, tantalum, tungsten and gold in the products they
manufacture and/or contract for manufacture. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">At Alcatel-Lucent, we recognize that some of our products may contain conflict minerals. As such, we
continue to implement due diligence practices to identify the sources of the minerals used in the components we purchase to manufacture our products, and to eliminate conflict minerals from our supply chain. As a part of this due diligence, we
conduct an annual survey asking our suppliers to report on their conflict minerals activity and, in particular, to identify the smelters involved in their own supply chain. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">We have designed our due diligence measures to conform in all material respects with the internationally recognized framework set forth in the
Organisation for Economic Co-operation and Development (OECD) <I>Due Diligence Guidance for Responsible Supply Chains of Minerals from Conflict-Affected and High-Risk Areas</I> (2013)&nbsp;and its related supplements for gold, tin, tantalum and
tungsten. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt" ALIGN="center">

<TR>
<TD WIDTH="73%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="25%"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt">
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt">ALCATEL-LUCENT CONFLICT MINERALS REPORT 2014</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" ALIGN="right">1</TD></TR></TABLE>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>1.3. &nbsp;&nbsp;How our supply chain works </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Below is a high-level view of how the supply chain works for a typical electronics company: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:10pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">


<IMG SRC="g934874g08y94.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
 </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">In reality, the supply chain is significantly more complex. Alcatel-Lucent products are typically made up of several
hundred different mechanical and electronic parts, with each sourced from as many as four different suppliers. A large proportion of these electronic parts is shared across most of the product families we deliver. As a result, precisely determining
the country of origin of the minerals used in our products&#146; components is a highly complex &#151; and sometimes difficult &#151; task. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:36pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:18pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>2. Our due diligence
measures </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>2.1. &nbsp;&nbsp;Step one: Establish strong internal management systems </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>2.1.1. Conflict Minerals Policy </I></B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:3pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">Published in 2012 and
available online at http://resources.alcatel-lucent.com/?cid=169613 , the Alcatel-Lucent Conflict Minerals Policy makes our position on conflict minerals clear to all stakeholders. Our Conflict Minerals Policy is regularly reviewed and updated as
necessary. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Specifically, our Conflict Minerals Policy outlines how Alcatel-Lucent is: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:11pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#9679;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:11pt">Recognizing the need to protect human rights and avoid contributing to the purchase of minerals from conflict zones; </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:11pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#9679;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:11pt">Involved in the efforts of the Global e-Sustainability Initiative (GeSI) to detect the presence of conflict minerals and eliminate the market for conflict
minerals through the development of tools to improve the traceability of products and minerals in the upstream supply chain; and </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt" ALIGN="center">

<TR>
<TD WIDTH="73%"></TD>

<TD WIDTH="25%"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt">
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt">ALCATEL-LUCENT CONFLICT MINERALS REPORT 2014</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" ALIGN="right">2</TD></TR></TABLE>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">


<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:11pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#9679;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:11pt">Focusing on its sphere of direct influence (i.e., the supply chain downstream from the minerals smelter), leveraging existing collaborative initiatives to
address the conflict minerals issues by: </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:11pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="14%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">o</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:11pt">Raising suppliers&#146; awareness of conflict minerals and having them identify the smelters that process the minerals they purchase; </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:11pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="14%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">o</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:11pt">Determining if identified smelters are &#145;conflict-free&#146; by using reliable information from industry associations; and </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:11pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="14%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">o</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:11pt">Engaging in dialogue with and requiring mitigation actions from suppliers who are inadvertently using conflict minerals or not determining the origin of the
minerals. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>2.1.2. Conflict Minerals Project Team and Steering Committee </I></B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:3pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">The Conflict Minerals Project Team within Alcatel-Lucent Operations ensures the company complies not only with all legal requirements and its own
Conflict Minerals Policy but also with the overall demands of our customers. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Project Team&#146;s responsibilities include: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:11pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#9679;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:11pt">Proposing and making updates to the Alcatel-Lucent Conflict Minerals Policy; </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:11pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:11pt">Setting yearly objectives for the Alcatel-Lucent Conflict Minerals Traceability Program; </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:11pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%">&nbsp;</TD>

<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:11pt">Participating actively in smelter outreach activities on behalf of the Conflict-Free Sourcing Initiative (CFSI); </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:11pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%">&nbsp;</TD>

<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:11pt">Managing conflict minerals data collection and engaging with suppliers for continuous improvements; and </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:11pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#9679;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:11pt">Preparing an annual Conflict Minerals Report for customers and authorities, which is posted on the Alcatel-Lucent website. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">Since June 2013, the Project Team has reported its progress to the Alcatel-Lucent Conflict Minerals Steering Committee, which includes representatives
from several key organizations within the company. The Steering Committee reviews the development of the Conflict Minerals Traceability Program and approves (or rejects) any proposals or updates to the Conflict Minerals Policy put forward by the
Project Team. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>2.1.3. Engagement with suppliers </I></B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:3pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">All suppliers who enter into agreements with Alcatel-Lucent are required, through contractual terms and conditions, to commit to the Electronics Industry
Citizenship Coalition (EICC) Code of Conduct Revision 5 and promote its requirements throughout their own supply chain. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">The mandatory terms and
conditions in our supplier contracts also include a specific section on conflict minerals requesting that suppliers provide data for supply chain traceability purposes. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt" ALIGN="center">

<TR>
<TD WIDTH="73%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="25%"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt">
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt">ALCATEL-LUCENT CONFLICT MINERALS REPORT 2014</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" ALIGN="right">3</TD></TR></TABLE>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>2.1.4. Communication with stakeholders </I></B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:3pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">Alcatel-Lucent has established a dedicated email account through which stakeholders can report any issues related to the use of conflict minerals or
obtain more information on the topic. Concerned parties can reach the Conflict Minerals Project Team directly at conflictminerals@alcatel-lucent.com. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>2.2.
&nbsp;&nbsp;Step two: Identify and assess risks in the supply chain </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>2.2.1. Risk identification </I></B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:3pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">Our technical experts analyze purchased item data sheets and conduct direct investigations with suppliers (as necessary) to determine if commodities
purchased by the company may contain conflict minerals. Three types of commodities are then defined: those with significant conflict minerals content; those with low conflict minerals content; and those with no conflict minerals content. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">The Project Team prepares a list of suppliers to survey for the concerned commodities and sends requests for information regarding conflict minerals to
the listed suppliers. To facilitate the transfer of information throughout the supply chain, suppliers are asked to provide their conflict minerals traceability information using the CFSI&#146;s Conflict Minerals Reporting Template (CMRT). Reminders
are sent to non-responsive suppliers and an escalation process is enacted when required. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">Through the CMRT, our suppliers identify the smelters
and/or refiners that produce the refined metals used in our supply chain. Alcatel-Lucent then uses that information to conduct an investigation into the minerals&#146; country of origin. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>2.2.2. Risk assessment </I></B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:3pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">While striving to avoid
sourcing minerals from conflict areas, Alcatel-Lucent does not want to prevent its suppliers from sourcing from legitimate mines located within the Democratic Republic of the Congo and its neighboring countries (as doing so could be detrimental to
the legitimate economies and populations of those countries). We are therefore focused on establishing minerals <I>traceability</I>. This involves compiling all collected CMRTs to establish a complete list of smelters identified in our supply chain.
</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">Leveraging available information such as that provided by the listed smelters previously identified as compliant with the CFSI&#146;s auditing
protocols and procedure, the Project Team is able to investigate and classify the minerals&#146; country-of-origin status according to the following categories: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:11pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#9679;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:11pt"><B>Level 1 countries:</B> Sources are supplied from countries with known active ore production that are not identified as plausible countries for the export,
smuggling or transit of conflict minerals. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:11pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#9679;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:11pt"><B>Level 2 countries:</B> Sources used are supplied from known or plausible countries for the export, smuggling or transit of conflict minerals.
</P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:11pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#9679;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:11pt"><B>Level 3 countries:</B> Sources used are potentially supplied from one or more of the nine countries bordering the Democratic Republic of the Congo.
</P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:11pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#9679;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:11pt"><B>Level 3 countries:</B> Sources used are potentially supplied from the Democratic Republic of the Congo. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:11pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#9679;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:11pt"><B>Recycled or scrap:</B> Sources used are supplied from recyclers or scrap suppliers. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt" ALIGN="center">

traceability practices are requested when their input does not meet the following expectations: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">Through its exchanges with suppliers, the Project Team promotes conflict minerals due diligence practices and mitigates risks by: </P>

<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:11pt">Promoting the usage of the CMRT as the most common and efficient tool to exchange conflict minerals data within the supply chain; </P></TD></TR></TABLE>

</P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>2.3.2. Continuous improvement </I></B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:3pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">To further improve the effectiveness of its Conflict Minerals Traceability Program, Alcatel-Lucent committed to achieving three main goals during the
2014 reporting period: broadening its reporting scope; improving its communications with suppliers; and adopting benchmarking best practices. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt" ALIGN="center">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">The results of the actions taken over the past year are as follows: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:11pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#9679;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:11pt"><B>Broadening reporting scope: </B>Although the number of suppliers assessed actually decreased in 2014 compared to the previous year, by better defining the
scope of the suppliers to be targeted, our assessments covered a larger purchasing spend. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:11pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#9679;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:11pt"><B>Improving communications with suppliers: </B>In 2014, we held 21 one-on-one training sessions to support our suppliers in improving their own due
diligence processes. We also informed our suppliers about the evolution of the CMRT and improved communications on the nature of the conflict minerals issue as a whole. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:11pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#9679;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:11pt"><B>Adopting benchmarking best practices: </B>To determine best practices in conflict minerals reporting, we conducted a thorough review of how other industry
leaders are presenting their conflict minerals processes and information. We integrated the findings into our own benchmarking and reporting for 2014, for example by improving the way we monitor our smelters&#146; reports and adding performance
indicators to our Conflict Minerals Report. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>2.4. &nbsp;&nbsp;Step four: Third-party audit of smelter/refiner due diligence practices </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">As a member of the CFSI, Alcatel-Lucent has access to the independent, third-party audits of smelters performed by the CFSI. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">In 2014, Alcatel-Lucent worked with the CFSI Smelter Engagement Team in an investigation seeking to identify <I>actual</I> smelters from presumed
smelters reported by the supply chain &#151; and then convince them to join the CFSI&#146;s conflict minerals auditing scheme. In many cases, the companies reported by the supply chain as smelters were not actual smelters but were intermediaries or
other companies. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>2.5. &nbsp;&nbsp;Step five: Report on supply chain due diligence </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Alcatel-Lucent reports annually on its supply chain due diligence through three different documents: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:11pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#9679;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:11pt">Additional information report (complement to Form 20-F); </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:11pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:18pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>3. Results of our supply chain due diligence </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>3.1. &nbsp;&nbsp;Results for 2014 </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>3.1.1. Material content of purchased
commodities </I></B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:3pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">In analyzing the material content of the commodities sourced to manufacture our products, it was determined that 435 of the 611
commodities included in our purchasing activities needed to be surveyed for conflict minerals. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The main conclusions from this analysis were: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:11pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#9679;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:11pt">Tin is present in most of the surface finish and soldering of our electronic and electromechanical parts; </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:11pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#9679;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:11pt">Gold is present in some integrated circuit chip connections and connectors finish; and </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:11pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#9679;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:11pt">Tantalum is present in some electronic components (in particular, capacitors) and radio frequency parts. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>3.1.2. Supplier reporting and conflict-free status </I></B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:3pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">Based on our commodity material content analysis, we identified relevant suppliers that provide us with products or components that could possibly
include one or more of tin, tantalum, tungsten or gold (collectively referred to as &#147;3TG&#148;). We then proceeded to survey 303 of these suppliers (representing 90 percent of our total purchasing spend) to determine the origin of the minerals
included in the purchased products or components. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt" ALIGN="center">

<TR>
<TD WIDTH="73%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="25%"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt">
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt">ALCATEL-LUCENT CONFLICT MINERALS REPORT 2014</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" ALIGN="right">7</TD></TR></TABLE>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">The chart below outlines the results of our supplier survey: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">


<IMG SRC="g934874g51y06.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
 </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">In total, 88 percent of the targeted suppliers responded to our request for information on their use of conflict
minerals. Of those, 30 percent were determined to have sourced minerals from conflict-free smelters (as determined by the CFSI) and 70 percent had an undetermined status (i.e., the supplier had not identified all of its smelters, or one or more of
the identified smelters had not been audited and determined as conflict-free by the CFSI). Among the suppliers determined to be conflict-free, 80 percent do not use tin, tantalum, tungsten and/or gold in the products or components they manufacture
or contract to manufacture. The remaining 20 percent use these metals in their products or components but know with full certainty that they did not originate from mines located in conflict regions. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">Among the 70 percent of respondents with an undetermined status, 20 percent had implemented all the improvement actions recommended by Alcatel-Lucent
and 50 percent had only a few actions still needing to be implemented. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt" ALIGN="center">

<TR>
<TD WIDTH="73%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="25%"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt">
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt">ALCATEL-LUCENT CONFLICT MINERALS REPORT 2014</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" ALIGN="right">8</TD></TR></TABLE>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>3.1.3. Smelter audit and country-of-origin determination </I></B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:3pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">Working closely with the CFSI, the smelters used throughout our supply chain are identified and analyzed according to the following process: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt" ALIGN="center">


<IMG SRC="g934874g28h35.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
 </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">(1) Company not yet identified as being an actual smelter. They are pointed to the CFSI for further investigation.
</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">(2) Based on the work of the CFSI as well as our own research, these companies have not been identified as actual smelters. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">(3) These smelters are not currently participating in any audit programs and have been contacted by the CFSI to join its audit program. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">Drawing on the information contained in the independent, third-party audits of smelters conducted by the CFSI, we identified the following smelters in
our supply chain: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:10pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:11pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">For smelters that had not been identified by the CFSI, we have asked our suppliers to encourage them to
join the CFSI. We have also reported these smelters to the CFSI so it can contact them directly. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>3.1.4. Conflict mineral status by product type </I></B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">At the product level, our conflict minerals status for 2014 is as follows: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TR STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt">
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt">ALCATEL-LUCENT CONFLICT MINERALS REPORT 2014</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" ALIGN="right">22</TD></TR></TABLE>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>3.2. Plans to improve due diligence for the 2015 reporting period </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">In 2015, Alcatel-Lucent intends to implement the following steps to further improve its conflict mineral due diligence measures: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:11pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:11pt"><B>Require suppliers to become conflict-free for tantalum:</B> In 2014, 43 of our 45 identified tantalum smelters were reported to be conflict-free by the
CFSI. We believe that sourcing this metal entirely from conflict-free smelters is achievable; as such, our primary goal for 2015 will be to require our suppliers to source tantalum from smelters that are reported as conflict free.
</P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:11pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:11pt"><B>Improve the management of part-level CMRTs:</B> We are currently in the process of developing an IT solution that would help us manage part-level CMRTs
(i.e., supplier declarations for each part delivered to us, rather than a single declaration covering all the parts delivered by the supplier), thereby improving data accuracy. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify"><B>Audit our own due diligence practices:</B> We intend to have our 2015 Conflict Minerals Report audited by an independent third party </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>
